      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DON'T BREW IT (3) stuck on well last time to finish 0.8 lengths back in third (26.49) at this track in a Grade 5 over 472m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Makes plenty of appeal. DIMINUTIVE LASS (1) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 26.85 beating Gate Two Sloy. Speedy beginner who should be in the action early off the inside. Should be in this for a long way. JUST BRAXTON (2) started big odds but ran a huge race last time when finishing 3rd over 472m at this track (26.88)in Mix. Was a winner the start prior in easier at Richmond. Can feature again. MIDNIGHT HOYEON (8) generally performs well over this distance.",
